ORDER: Defendant Anglo Irish Bank Corporation Limited is directed to respond to Plaintiffs' June 20, 2011 letter by Wednesday, June 22, 2011 at 5 p.m. (Signed by Judge Paul G. Gardephe on 6/20/2011) (tro) (Entered: 06/21/2011)
512011-11-29
 MEMORANDUM OPINION & ORDER: For the reasons stated above, Defendant is a "foreign state" within the meaning of the FSIA. Plaintiffs have not demonstrated that Ireland has waived sovereign immunity for purposes of this action or that any exc eption to sovereign immunity is applicable. Accordingly, this action is dismissed for lack of subject matter jurisdiction and Plaintiffs' motion for a preliminary injunction is denied as moot. The Clerk of the Court is directed to terminate the motion and to close this case..  (Signed by Judge Paul G. Gardephe on 11/28/2011) (cd)

  












